body:
> Can you provide more information about what test is failing specifically, any logs related to the failing test, and hopefully a stack trace?

I wish I could, but as I stated in the update, the tests now pass for me, so I can't see where the error is being produced. I could recall from memory, but I doubt that will be helpful.

@kesar do you still have this issue locally?

@kesar
After reviewing [`ethers.js` documentation](https://docs.ethers.io/v5/api/contract/contract/#Contract-functionsCall) for method calls, I believe your issue is that the contract call is either reverting or that you are requiring gas to submit the transaction.

<img width="745" alt="Screen Shot 2021-05-03 at 11 34 10 AM" src="https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/37757724/116904568-7c95bf00-ac03-11eb-93db-d93c3f326294.png">

@platocrat - I have a strong feeling this is not related to our tooling, but rather trying to do an invalid call. I would check that 
1. The contract deployment succeeded (there is code at the address you are calling)
2. The interface you are using to call the contract is correct
